'author_association': 'CONTRIBUTOR', 'active_lock_reason': None, 'body': '**Describe the bug**
Full screen Client Web UI launched from Content Designer reports errors when ENFORCE_VERIFIED_IDENTITY is true. The first request after a page refresh works, but subsequent requests do not. See screenshot.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10953374/163893453-f9ac4a60-12e9-40b8-b89c-514433109e02.png)


**To Reproduce**
Set ENFORCE_VERIFIED_IDENTITY to true and use the Web client to interact with the bot.

**Expected behavior**
Web client should send JWT token in idtokenjwt session attribute for all interactions. 

NOTE: Installing a separate Lex Web UI stack with enable login enabled has not sure problem. This issue relates only to the QnABot wen client (not separate Lex Web UI)

**Please complete the following information about the solution:**

Content Designer "Test All" feature fails to run tests when setting ENFORCE_VERIFIED_IDENTITY is true.  
QnaBot requires a valid JWT token in the Lex request.

**To Reproduce**
Set ENFORCE_VERIFIED_IDENTITY to `true` and run Test All.
View results.. Each test case reports that the user identity could not be verified.

**Expected behavior**
Tests should run using the identity of logged in user.

**Please complete the following information about the solution:**
- v5.1.2

*Description of changes:*
Vendor the `witch.js` helper

`witch.js` is a lambda layer that performs some magic to upload the web site contents.
Previously it was provided as a external lambda layer. This PR adds the layer definition to the repository.

## Testing

- [X] Deploy the updated template
- [X] Verify the website contents

Vendor the `witch.js` helper

Vendor the `witch.js` helper

Previously it was provided as a external lambda layer. This PR adds the layer definition to the repository.

Vendor the `witch.js` helper

*Description of changes:*
Vendor the `witch.js` helper

`witch.js` is a lambda layer that performs some magic to upload the web site contents.
Previously it was provided as a external lambda layer. This PR adds the layer definition to the repository.

- [X] Verify the website contents

Further updates the the Content Security Policy

- fixed Kendra Webcrawler data source sync issue by adding support to check for Kendra webcrawler data source {status} before initiating sync
- fixed issue where the Kendra Webcrawler data source {settings} page in Kendra console was resulting in a blank page - by updating configuraton parameters for data source create and update steps
- updated API Gateway Integration Request setting (for Kendra Webcrawler POST method) to include HTTP header to support asynchronous execution of the backend Lambda function
- updated status reporting for Kendra Webcrawler
- updated build setup in makefiles
- updated changelog

Submitting this PR with these changes for review.

- updated status reporting for Kendra Webcrawler
- updated build setup in makefiles
- updated changelog

Submitting this PR with these changes for review.

- updated build setup in makefiles
- updated changelog
